    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-02T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/813: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-02T23:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 2, 1935—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 2—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Arthur Young informed me today that Chinese Government was about to decide to
                    make a unit of principal banks of issue and to take over all silver. He [asked]
                    what attitude American banks would take. I told him I could not tell nor was I
                    in a position to advise them. I suggested that he approach banks directly which
                    he will do on behalf of Ministry of Finance. He said Hong Kong &amp; Shanghai
                    Bank was prepared to cooperate by turning over its silver holdings against
                    Central Bank notes on advice of Leith-Ross, that an Order in Council is in
                    process of preparation to enable it to cooperate in above described way.</p>
                <p>This would of course mean that the Chinese Government would take over all silver
                    reserves now held by private Chinese banks and such foreign banks as will
                    voluntarily cooperate. Young said Chinese Government’s decision would be made in
                    next 3 or 4 days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
